I think it's safe to say that if corruption, or any other form of it survives into Shadowlands, WoW is dead to me
Corruption in a nutshell: "We heard you hated the RNG of titanforging.  So here's a new system with RNG on top of RNG, and WAY more power creep to go along with it!"
"Also if you indulge in it too much it'll kill you."
Wait, what?
"HAVEFUNKBYEEEEEEEEEEE"
What's with all these RNGs? Are they planning to become a roguelike?
The prevailing theory is that the WoW B team responsible for this expansion, and possibly Legion, were pulled from the Diablo team
As a result, when designing this (maybe last) expansion, they brought with them design philosophies from Diablo
But the problem is that they implemented some of the worst parts of Diablo's design into WoW, without the good sides of a dungeon crawler to negate them
Games like diablo usually have a lot of RNG when it comes to loot, in terms of power, stats, etc.  But they throw it at you all day long.
MMOs dish them out at a slower pace.  So combine the two and you have a far worse feeling system
I can imagine.
It doesn't balance out.
Corruption if extremely frustrating
First, the gear has to corrupt.  Then it needs to be the corruption you want.  And then you might want a specific tier of corruption
Titanforging was just "did it forge, and how many ilvls?"
And that was already polarizing enough.
I had a piece of gear that would generally be HORRIBLE for my character
The stats were wrong, so it would be a downgrade, even though it was an item lvl increase
But thanks to the corruption it rolled, it was a 10% increase to my dps.  10%.  That's ABSURD.
I'll stop it there.  I need to work on reeling in my rants.  Suffice to say, there are so many things about WoW that frustrate me at the moment that I could rant for a whole day.
